{
  "texts": [
    "Similarly, for our TriviaQA experiments, the task is to either answer the query or abstaining from answering by responding with \"I don't know\".",
    "The first reward function we consider assigns a reward of +2 for the correct answer, -3 for an incorrect answer, and -3 for abstaining.",
    "The second reward function assigns 0 for abstaining, and is the same otherwise.",
    "For the first reward function, P unf (y) corresponds to randomly guessing an answer, because randomly guessing an answer yields a higher average reward than abstaining from answering.",
    "In contrast, for the second reward function, P unf (y) corresponds to abstaining from answering, because abstaining from answering on average yields higher reward than randomly guessing an answer."
  ]
}